an tank but would rather have someone else do it if at all possible?<br><br>Just wondering.. found myself (40 ranger) and a 45 beastlord in a group yesterday... and I was tanking. (It was so easy getting aggro, I'd have had a hard time NOT doing so.. so I just took it in stride *grin*)  Should i have worked to let him tank?   I've seen a few groups with just a beastlord as their tank work well (giants in Frontier Mountains, for ex *waves at Band of Dreamers*).<br><br><br><br> <p><center><i><a href=mailto:kyrial_moonlight@lycos.com>Kyrial Moonlight</a><BR><font color=white>A light shines upon us all.</font></I><P>Wyrd Windwalker.  Kyrial Darkflame.</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukelisk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kelisk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No, YOU'RE evil</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/8/02 6:58:37 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://216.40.201.155/s/games/ultima/MON16.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: beastlords.. tanks?</span><hr size=1> We can be batshit insane as tanks, so long as we're in the right environment. Besides having decent HP and AC ourselves, once we start getting low we can back away and the pet's practically another tank, since we can CHeal with our level-up spells. <p><img src="http://publish.hometown.aol.com/bseh42/images/kelsig.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utwotribes.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twotribes</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Troll</span><br>  Posts: 390<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/8/02 11:12:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: beastlords.. tanks?</span><hr size=1> As I understand it Beastlords do NOT get The AC bonus that monks get for being under 14 stones(pounds). If you are only wearing leather it may be difficult to avoid massive damage on a lot of mobs.<br><br>have not played a beastlord nor do i know any over 21 (level). I would tend to say if they cant wear at least chain they proably should avoid getting and holding agro in a group ( unless they are better equiped then partners). Their pet is close to their level with buffs ( I guess at some levels higher even). Sounds to me like the intent is to have the pet do the melee beat down. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufalzure.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falzure</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/9/02 4:15:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: beastlords.. tanks?</span><hr size=1> That depends what level you are <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     Beastlords are techincally hybrids between monks and shamans, however keep in mind that although you get many melee defensive and offensive skills, they are capped much lower than your average melee.<br><br>But of course you have your Warder so its not really a big deal <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   .  My advice is to let your Warder tank as much as possible because A) He's tougher than you, and B) You can heal him easyer than yourself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   .<br><br>With that said, I would estimate that on thier own (no warder) Beastlords &quot;tank&quot; about on par with a Bard (no songs), although this may shift back and forth depending on your level and which equipment you use.<br><br>But, as I said before you have a Warder, and Warder = ownz <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   .<br><br>ta ta,<br><br>- Falzure<br><br>Minor ED. note: Bards like their plate wearing parents have more mitigation than avoidance, where as Bestlords have more avoidance than mitigation like their parents, Monks.  Because of this your ability to tank will also be dependant on the type of enemy you are fighting.  due to low HP caster = bad. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ufalzure.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Falzure</A> at: 3/9/02 4:19:24 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/10/02 11:28:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: beastlords.. tanks?</span><hr size=1> Beastlords, in the right environment, can out tank anything... because they can back up and let the pet take the beating, then complete heal... at 20, I, a rogue, with a 25 beastlord and a 25 bard, too down Curfang repeatedly, a 25 to 28 underconned mob.  We did this by rushing curfang, then backing off when too damaged, with the bard twisting heal and mana.  The pet could tank nearly forever against Curfang, then we'd zome back in and take him down when rested up.  <br><br>Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=crowe>Crowe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/21/02 12:02:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: beastlords.. tanks?</span><hr size=1> Aye, beastlords can tank fer a bit, or even fer a long time if in the right situaltion.  I put myself on par with a ranger fer normal tank more--hit fer hit.  But there are two differences.  One, as mentioned before, I have a pet fer backup and healing purposes.  Nothing like bein able to take a couple steps back and have a new look at the situation without leavin the melee.<br>Second, we do not taunt.  Many ferget that, and ferget that is is often VERY hard to get agro off another without that skill.  Been in groups as a beastlord as the only melee type with lots of casters and as they lay waste ta the enemy, they get agroed.  Hard ta draw the attention of that enemy back onta me after that.  Gotta wait fer the puppy ta beat on it fer a bit and then back down.  (Of course, most just cast ANOTHER major spell and get agro again.)  I think this is the most common misconseption fer the beastlord and one that needs to be addressed when entering a group.  Simply say &quot;I cannot taunt, but my dog (gator, bear, squirrel, whatever) can.&quot;<br><br>Crowe<br>Clan of Brothers<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukhiraz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khiraz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/21/02 3:07:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: beastlords.. tanks?</span><hr size=1> One small thing (bah, okay, two) to point out to the non-beastlords reading:<br><br>All this mention of backing up and letting the warder tank is when we SOLO. When in groups, our pet does not automatically top the hate list when her master steps back; the mob will follow the usual rules for choosing targets.<br><br>Regarding the taunting, Crowe's right, we don't have it. However, there are quite a few spells we get almost from the start that serve well in that regard. Flash of Light, Tainted Breath, and especially Drowsy generate a lot of hate. Chain-casting one of these (easily done due to the low mana cost) can work quite well in getting a mob off someone it shouldn't be on. I wouldn't recommend using this technique to play main tank in a group, though, because our weapon delay resets after casting as the other hybrids used to do. Chain-casting in that situation would mean a lot of swings lost, and may even cost the main tank the aggro he's been working so hard to keep.<br><br>Khiraz Spiritbinder<br>Patriarch of Cabilis<br>Skathris Ven'Sho <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uhoraciofv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HoracioFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/21/02 6:44:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> strange thing</span><hr size=1> I was wondering if the pet and the beastlord are on the same hate list. Ok a good friend of mine Vothe has been on 3 kael raids with me. The first raid the MA was a 54 warrior. For some reason Vothe (51 bst) seem's to gain agro and is almost imposible to taunt off of him. I don't have my damage turned on but I find it hard to belive he would be dealing SO much damage with just himself to generate the kind of hate he dose. The only thing I can figure is that his damage and his warders damage both transfer hate onto himself. Not to mention his warder was casting also.. but since the warder itself dose not agro if PC's are in meele dose that hate transfer to the BST?. Its not that he dosnt take a licking and keep on ticking.. but it dose tend to throw the healers into a frenzy <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . Mabey if I can find out how the agro is gained by said BST I can figure out a way to keep it from happening. Any input would be apreciated thank you. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukratetheswifttail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krate The Swift Tail</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.geocities.com/thrawk/Krate.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/22/02 10:41:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: beastlords.. tanks?</span><hr size=1> I'll give you my 2 copper on Beastlords and their pets.  Alone, without their Warder, a Beastlord is more useless then OOM Wizard.  They would get clobbered toe to toe with most things they are going to try and tank after level 40.  Now if they are not getting hit and they are just adding their own damage to the mob then they are nice because even without a warder they do a little more damage then Bards Melee.  If you’re in a raid or large encounter and the Beastlord is tanking with no pet, someone better be hitting the evac button.<br><br>Now a Beastlord and its warder are a different story.  That little pet is one tough SOB.  Me a level 35 Monk at the time took out a level 37 Beastlord without his pet in the Bazaar arena in under a minute.  I then fought the warder and had to use mend to finish it.  I could not of defeated the warder if the Beastlord was healing it.<br><br>It’s these reasons that Beastlords are great in XP groups or solo and suck ass on raids.<br><br>So to answer the question about tanking in-groups, if the Beastlords pet is tanking then it’s good.  If the Beastlord is tanking without the pet after 40 then it’s bad.  You may as well let an Enchanter pet tank rather then a lone Beastlord.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvothe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vothe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/22/02 11:46:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bioware.com/_global/images/sidenav/tob_icon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: beastlords.. tanks?</span><hr size=1> Here's the deal. The pet does add to our agro, Hence when I send pet in giant summons me. I hit for 50's proc for 50...pet quads (about 1 ni 20 attacks) for 53's procs for 60's Now, if I am in tanking with pet all I need to do is cast a low lvl poison spell and instand HATE, and I Mean HATE...I can pull the mob off any caster any time, unless that caster is also spaming, which he/she won't do long...LOADING please wait. no as for Kael Horacio, about 6 months ago vernant patched warriors taunt so it sucked against red mobs, IE they ignore you to a large degree. that is why you cannot out agro me with ease. Can we tank/should we tank....We can tank with proper gear. we get a small bonus to ac for the leather we wear, but we have no weight restriction like monks. I have mid 900 ac with 2500 hp's max buffed. But should we....I think every class has it's place, BST deal a lot of dmg (with pet) (like a wizard FM all the time ;p) but for all of this, leather armor is no replacment for metal, and warriors have the edge and should be the tank. but in a pinch, we can tank, and if brave can use our skills to pull mobs off slowers etc untill tank can get mob off us....saving the casters lives and puttin ourselves in the line of danger, since we tank better than said caster <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And in responce to the above poster, I think he needs to play one b4 he judges one.  <p><img src="http://www.bioware.com/_global/images/sidenav/tob_icon.jpg" border="0"><Br>"Lord of beasts, Stalking the shadows for blood and murder"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvothe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vothe</A> at: 3/22/02 11:56:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=