es/sig001.jpg"><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usheerz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheerz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/27/02 10:50:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=54.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: beastlords.. tanks?</span><hr size=1> Actually Qixx, have you fought with a higher level BL??<br>We do about par with ranger in damage with warder, maybe a little more. Draw very little aggro due to the spreading of damage between BL and warder. <br>Check out the spells Savagery and Spiritual Purity, you might want the first one cast on you since it stacks with I think everything, SP stacks with all clarity spells in the line and all cleric spells, but does not stack with druids PotC I believe. Yes, we do suck at taking damage at higher levels just as any other non tank class. <br>I do agree that if we are not allowed to use our warder we are a little low on the damage output, but we can have our pets in places where other classes get a NoNo since it is a BUFF and can be clicked off at any time. we have the spell Summon Companion and with firm control over the /pet back off button we can have pretty good control over what it does. Ok, it isn't fool proof, but a BL that hasn't learned to control his pet by that level should try something else.<br>BL as tank i would have to say Only if there is NO other melee availiable and we would need some healing to be kept alive. We should tank no more than you want the rogue to tank.<br><br>Oh and last.. i believe our pet has an unresistable stun procc to be used too, i'll have to see if it is when i get to that level. <p><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=77883" target="new"><im